issue_obverse_figure_description_s: Seal of a hand bleeding after picking from a thornbush with motto SUSTINE VEL AHSTINE (Either survive or refrain).
issue_obverse_legend_s: THE UNITED STATES OF NORTH AMERICA | FIVE DOLLARS | FIVE DOLLARS. THE BEARER is entitled to receive FIVE Spanish milled DOLLARS, or an equal Sum in Gold or Silver, according to a Re-solution of CONGRESS of the 14th January, 1779. Five Dollars.
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Nature print of fever few leaf.
issue_reverse_legend_s: FIVE DOLLARS. | Printed by HALL and SEL-LERS. 1779.
